I made a less file with the following content:

```less
@import 'font-awesome/less/font-awesome.less';
@import 'bootstrap/less/bootstrap.less';

button.open {
	.btn;
	.btn-default;

	i, span {
		.fa;
		.fa-lg;
		.fa-folder-open;
	}
}
```

But got this error:

```bash
Potentially unhandled rejection [2] .fa-folder-open is undefined
````

It happens with any icon, because apparently there aren´t any mixin for icons.

The solution is change the icons.less content from:

```less
.@{fa-css-prefix}-folder-open:before { content: @fa-var-folder-open; }
```

to

```less
.@{fa-css-prefix}-folder-open { &:before { content: @fa-var-folder-open; } }
```

What do you think about this solution? Can you make a fix?

