   router-id HOST_IP_ADDRESS; 
   local-address HOST_IP_ADDRESS;
   local-as AS_NUMBER;
   peer-as AS_NUMBER;
   group-updates false;

   family {
        ipv4 mpls-vpn;
        }

   neighbor NEIGHBOR_1 {
 	description NEIGHBOR_1_NAME;
	}

   neighbor NEIGHBOR_2 {
 	description NEIGHBOR_2_NAME;
	}

   process agent {
      encoder text;
      run /agent.py;
   }
}
```

<!--- You can also use gist.github.com links for larger files -->

##### SUMMARY
<!--- Explain the problem briefly -->
When the labelled route is withdrawn and announced with different next-hop and within few milliseconds, ExaBgp is ignoring the announce and is sending only the withdraw to the Bgp peer.

##### STEPS TO REPRODUCE
<!---
For bugs, please if possible, please run with the "-d" option and provide the full output,
If not possible, please provide the full fault section as reported by ExaBGP
-->

1. withdraw route 216.58.217.4/32 rd 44:1000000 next-hop 10.0.42.3 extended-community [ target:44:1000000 ] label 44
2. announce route 216.58.217.4/32 rd 44:1000000 next-hop 10.0.44.7 extended-community [ target:44:1000000 ] label 44
The commands are sent to ExaBgp within few milliseconds.

##### EXPECTED RESULTS
<!--- What did you expect to happen when running the steps above? -->
Bgp peer should have been sent with the route with the new next-hop

##### ACTUAL RESULTS
<!--- What actually happened? -->
Bgp peer received only the withdraw and not the announce that followed.

##### IMPORTANCE
<!-- Please let us know if the issue is affecting you in a production environment -->
It is impacting our production environment.

